  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Awareness raising about COVID-19 with NFI distribution for vulnerable families at Homs Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">the project aims to reduce the risk of an outbreak of Covid-19 virus , and aid the precautionary measures of the Syrian Government to suppress and slow the transaction of the virus through quick and effective intervention in WASH sector, the scope of work will include 3 rural areas of Homs city (Hassyeh - Masskaneh - Baba Amr) in addition to some neighborhood in the city it self. the initial target of beneficiaries from all activities will round up to 8250 person of the most vulnerable population with emphasis on Women-Headed families and IDPs , the project will cover the need of those beneficiaries starting from providing them with essential hygiene items , fixing the sanitation facilities and preform a daily sterilization to a 12 shelters located in the areas of intervention , and ending with conducting a safe and informative awareness sessions (whether group sessions or individual sessions) those activities will result a more protected communities in the rural areas , and more prepared shelter centers to face the global pandemic of Covid-19</narrative>
  </description>
